## Git commands
##git setup
a. Git New Repo  setup (existing code in dev machine a new repo with no codr in git remote)
- Run`git init` from the command at your code directory
- copy remote url from git remote
- run `git remote add origin <url>`

**b. Cloning a new repo (You want to get/download all the code from git remote)**

- get in the directory where you want to clone the app
- run `git clone <url> <foldername>`
- this will setup `<reponame> or <folder name>` folder at your clonned location

## commit command

**a. adding the changes**

-run `git add.` or `git add <file name>`

**b. commit message**

-run after`adding the changes` this step, `git commit -m "<your message>"`


## git operation (push or pull)

**a. git push operation**
-run `git push origin [-u] <localBranchName>[:<remoteBranchName>]`(default branch will only get pushed (main))

**b. git pull operation**

- check if codes are commited or not, if not commited, commit your changes first
after commit run, `git pull origin <remoteBranchName>`
-If there are conflicts, resolve the conflicts annuallly,
- atfer every conflict resoulation, commit the changes


* git branch
**a. create a new Branch**

-run `git checkout -b <branchName>` it will create a new branch from current branch

**b. list all branches*

